definition[0]: to arrive at a particular place, after going to other places first
example[0]: I took a long holiday in Italy and finished up in Rome.
definition[1]: to get into a particular state or situation as the result of what you have done, especially without planning or expecting it
example[1]: He tried to bribe a police officer and finished up in jail.
example[2]: Brett got into a fight and finished up with a broken wrist.
definition[2]: to eat or drink all the rest of something, so there is none left
example[3]: Come on, finish up your drinks!
